{
  "global": "Apply the effusion (Knudsen) regime to find the flux-weighted velocity distribution of escaping N₂ molecules, compute their biased translational KE and unbiased rotational energy, then sum to obtain E_avg.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Establish the flux-weighted distribution for escaping molecules",
      "atomics": [
        "Write the Maxwell-Boltzmann single-particle velocity distribution f(v_x, v_y, v_z) = (m/2πk_BT)^(3/2) exp(-mv²/2k_BT)",
        "State that in the effusion (Knudsen) regime the rate of molecules escaping with velocity (v_x, v_y, v_z) is proportional to v_x · f(v) for v_x > 0, giving a flux-weighted distribution",
        "Factor the flux-weighted distribution: p(v_x) ∝ v_x exp(-mv_x²/2k_BT) for v_x>0 (biased), p(v_y) ∝ exp(-mv_y²/2k_BT) and p(v_z) ∝ exp(-mv_z²/2k_BT) (unbiased Maxwellian)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute average translational kinetic energy of escaping molecules",
      "atomics": [
        "Normalize p(v_x): the biased x-distribution is p(v_x) = 2β v_x exp(-βv_x²) with β = m/(2k_BT), a Rayleigh distribution",
        "Evaluate <(1/2)mv_x²>_esc = mβ ∫₀^∞ v_x³ exp(-βv_x²) dv_x = mβ · 1/(2β²) = m/(2β) = k_BT",
        "Evaluate <(1/2)mv_y²>_esc = k_BT/2 and <(1/2)mv_z²>_esc = k_BT/2 from the unbiased Maxwellian",
        "Sum: <KE_trans>_esc = k_BT + k_BT/2 + k_BT/2 = 2k_BT"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute average internal (rotational) energy of escaping N₂ molecules",
      "atomics": [
        "Note that the effusion selection criterion (v_x > 0) acts only on translational velocity, leaving rotational and vibrational states unmodified",
        "Apply equipartition to N₂ (diatomic, 2 active rotational DoF at temperature T): <E_rot>_esc = 2 × (1/2)k_BT = k_BT"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Sum all energy contributions to obtain E_avg",
      "atomics": [
        "Add translational and rotational contributions: E_avg = <KE_trans>_esc + <E_rot>_esc = 2k_BT + k_BT",
        "State final result: E_avg = 3k_BT"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Confirm no PdV enthalpy correction: gas escapes into vacuum (zero external pressure), so no work term is added to the molecule's energy budget",
    "Check limiting case: if N₂ were monatomic (0 internal DoF), the formula would give 2k_BT, recovering the known monatomic effusion result"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Weight the Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution by v_x to obtain the flux-selected distribution, compute <KE_trans>_esc = 2k_BT via the Rayleigh integral, add equipartition rotational energy k_BT for N₂, yielding E_avg = 3k_BT",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Establish flux-weighted distribution for escaping N₂ molecules",
        "atomics": [
          "Write f(v) = (m/2πk_BT)^(3/2) exp(-mv²/2k_BT) as the equilibrium MB distribution",
          "Multiply by v_x to get the effusion-rate distribution: dΦ ∝ v_x (m/2πk_BT)^(3/2) exp(-mv²/2k_BT) d³v for v_x > 0",
          "Factor into p(v_x) ∝ v_x exp(-βv_x²) [Rayleigh, biased] and standard Gaussians in v_y, v_z [unbiased], with β ≡ m/(2k_BT)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Compute <KE_trans>_esc = 2k_BT",
        "atomics": [
          "Normalize Rayleigh distribution: p(v_x) = 2β v_x exp(-βv_x²) on [0,∞)",
          "Compute <(1/2)mv_x²> = mβ · (1/2β²) = m/(2β) = k_BT using ∫₀^∞ v_x³ e^{-βv_x²} dv_x = 1/(2β²)",
          "Read off <(1/2)mv_y²> = <(1/2)mv_z²> = k_BT/2 from the unmodified Maxwellian",
          "Sum: <KE_trans>_esc = k_BT + k_BT/2 + k_BT/2 = 2k_BT"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Compute <E_rot>_esc = k_BT for N₂",
        "atomics": [
          "Argue that rotational state selection is independent of v_x effusion criterion, so escaping molecules have equilibrium rotational energies",
          "Apply equipartition to 2 rotational DoF of N₂: <E_rot> = 2 × (1/2)k_BT = k_BT"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Add contributions: E_avg = 2k_BT + k_BT = 3k_BT",
        "atomics": [
          "Combine biased translational KE (2k_BT) and unbiased rotational energy (k_BT)",
          "Report E_avg = 3k_BT"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Verify zero external-pressure boundary: molecules escape into vacuum, so no enthalpy (PV) correction applies and energy carried = thermal energy only",
      "Cross-check monatomic limit: setting rotational DoF = 0 recovers the textbook effusion result <KE_trans>_esc = 2k_BT"
    ]
  }
}
```

